Words of affirmation is like second for me whereas for my husband itâ€™s not even on the list. Luckily physical touch is high for both of us so I try to use that often since itâ€™s the language we both speak in. I would suggest trying to incorporate a language that he speaks into your vocabulary because it will help you a lot to feel that love more freely.

Words of affirmation is tough. There arenâ€™t a lot of men who like to speak their emotions and women seem to really love to hear it. There isnâ€™t much room for compromise since forcing someone to use words of affirmation can feel exactly that, super forced. 

Do you speak through text often? I find my hubby is much more eloquent and loving verbally through text than in person. Since Iâ€™ve noticed that Iâ€™ve just started screencapping some of the sweet things he says to me and saving to look at later when Iâ€™m feeling needy or annoyed with him etc. I also find that continuing to use words of affirmation myself towards him tends to make me feel good about it, even if he isnâ€™t speaking them back.

All in all itâ€™s tough to balance but the key is compromise and finding a middle ground where you can feel loved by him in a way thatâ€™s meaningful to you and in turn love him the same way back. Since there are different love languages at play here, try finding one you both can speak with.
